%I A316195 #24 Jun 22 2026 08:11:51
%S A316195 0,0,2,1,18,45,441,2681,23833
%N A316195 Number of self-avoiding polygons with perimeter 2*n and sides = 1 that have vertex angles from the set +-Pi/5, +-3*Pi/5, not counting rotations and reflections as distinct.
%C A316195 Holes are excluded, i.e., the boundary path may nowhere touch or intersect itself.
%C A316195 From _Anton Pirogov_, Jun 17 2026: (Start)
%C A316195 Also number of free simple matchstick polygons with perimeter 2*n on the cyclotomic ring Z[zeta_10] whose vertex turning angles are all odd multiples of Pi/5.
%C A316195 The new terms a(8)-a(9) were obtained as a sub-count of the enumeration of free simple matchstick polygons on Z[zeta_10] using the tilezz library. (End)
%H A316195 Contest Organizers, <a href="http://www.recmath.org/contest/Snakes/index.php">Al Zimmermann's Programming Contests - Snakes on a Plane</a>, Fall 2006.
%H A316195 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="http://www.randomwalk.de/sequences/a316195.htm">Illustration of polygons of perimeter <= 14</a>.
%H A316195 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://github.com/apirogov/tilezz">tilezz</a> - exact cyclotomic geometry library including a polygon enumerator.
%H A316195 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://ratdb.app.pirogov.de">Rat Explorer</a> - interactive database of cyclotomic matchstick polygons.
%H A316195 Anton Pirogov, <a href="https://github.com/apirogov/tilezz-ratdb">RatDB datasets</a> - reproducible datasets containing the enumerated polygons.
%Y A316195 Cf. A306175, A258206, A266549, A284869.
%K A316195 nonn,walk,more,changed
%O A316195 1,3
%A A316195 _Hugo Pfoertner_, Jun 26 2018
%E A316195 a(8)-a(9) from _Anton Pirogov_, Jun 17 2026
